The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, December 05, 2002 				 Assault heat on Kerala judge
																								Kochi, Dec. 4 (PTI): A sitting judge of Kerala High Court is in the eye of a controversy over his alleged assault on a motorcyclist.																								The All-India Lawyers Union has urged the high court chief justice to take exemplary action against Justice J.M. James.																								The incident occurred two days ago when a youth refused to let James car overtake his motorcycle. An angry James allegedly jumped out of the car and assaulted Saneesh.																								After the alleged incident, Saneesh was admitted in a hospital with severe ear pain. Police sources said he complained about a non-cognisable offence.																								The unions state general-secretary N.A. Ali in a statement here has demanded strong action against Justice James.
